{
  "stem": "8252.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Other things were they were grabbing people in the street, grabbing Jews in the street and putting them to work, some dirty work like washing, washing the, stones of the street and so on.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, they had fun.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They just making fun with the Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember, that was even before I had that yellow armband because I was going on the main street with a-- with a Gentile friend of mine who happened to have a very long nose.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And a German officer stops us and asks us where is the post office?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had this-- you know, when you're in your early 20s-- I was 22 at that time-- you like to play jokes.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So, of course, we showed him the other way.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We wouldn't show him the right way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was a German.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was the enemy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he looks at both of us and he says to me, you won't have any trouble, but he turns to the Gentile, you better be careful because you're Jewish.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You Jews, you're going to suffer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was a German officer who stopped us in the streets in September 1939.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Very soon thereafter, somebody in the German command obviously wanted to make some money.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there is a poster in the city that says that if you have a Polish foreign passport, they will extend it for a certain amount of money.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Now, that was fine except that you had to stand in line in the street and that was in dan-- that was a danger because they were always counting Jews to get to some work or something like that.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was not the danger of life yet at this point.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
